\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 SimpleBrowser is a little application which show how to use the Cocoa NSBrowser class.  The application implements a file system browser using NSBrowser as the display mechanism.  The browser lets you navigate the file system, and launch and open documents and applications.  This sample code demonstrates:\
\
	\'a5 How to display simple data in a browser\
	\'a5 Using a custom NSBrowserCell subclass for display.\
	\'a5 Filling a browser using the "lazy" delegation style.\
	\'a5 Other simple NSBrowser features (eg. handling single click actions).\
\
