\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 The AppController object is the delegate of the 
\f0\b fsBrowser
\f1\b0  object.  A browser delegate must implement 
\f0\b browser:willDisplayCell:atRow:column:
\f1\b0  and either of the methods 
\f0\b browser:numberOfRowsInColumn:
\f1\b0  or 
\f0\b browser:createRowsForColumn:inMatrix:
\f1\b0 .   Our AppController implements 
\f0\b browser:numberOfRowsInColumn:
\f1\b0 , and thus 
\f0\b fsBrowser
\f1\b0  lazily loads it's data.  Since loading a cell in the browser involves touching the disk, it seems appropriate for the browser to be lazy.  \
\
AppController sets the single/double click actions of the browser to be 
\f0\b browserSingleClick:
\f1\b0 , and 
\f0\b browserDoubleClick:
\f1\b0  respectively.  When a single click is received the browser displays information about the current selection.  A double click on a file will open the file, while a double click on an application result in a launch of the program.\
